<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/LE_GW_003.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  <p align="left">1.  How well do you know the person you are writing to?<g id="t1">A.  You have known them for a long time.</g><g id="t2">B.  You have been writing to them for a long time.</g><g id="t3">C.  You have only just met them.</g><g id="t4">D.  You have never met them.</g></p>
  <p align="left">2.  What style of letter should you write?<g id="t5">A.  formal</g><g id="t6">B.  informal</g></p>
  <p align="left">3.  What do you have to do in this letter?<g id="t7">A.  make arrangements</g><g id="t8">B.  provide information</g><g id="t9">C.  explain a situation</g><g id="t10">D.  request information</g><g id="t11">E.  offer advice</g></p>
  <p align="left">4.  How many points do you have to cover in this letter?<g id="t12">A.  one</g><g id="t13">B.  two</g><g id="t14">C.  three</g><g id="t15">D.  four</g><g id="t16">E.  five</g></p>
  <p align="left">5.  What personal information would it be appropriate toinclude in this letter?<g id="t17">A.  your nationality</g><g id="t18">B.  where you live</g><g id="t19">C.  some details about your family</g><g id="t20">D.  your life history</g><g id="t21">E.  what you do</g></p>
  <p align="left">6.  According to the writing task, what do you have to askthe person you are writing to?<g id="t22">A.  how they spend their free time</g><g id="t23">B.  where they live</g><g id="t24">C.  what they look like</g><g id="t25">D.  what they do</g><g id="t26">E.  what their future plans are</g></p>
